reviewText: I like it very informational. Only thing is that the quality of the dvd is not that great. very jumpy and pauses.

For a primer on caching, this was really good.  Unfortunately, as the disclaimer at the beginning stated, it was sopmewhat dated.  Since it came out about 15 years ago, there has been a lot of progress on caching technology that is obviously not addressed.  That of course can't be helped.  It does have some very good ideas though, and it you're considering caching food, supplies and weapons it's not a bad place to start.
